headline: S&P 500 Gains and Losses Today: Regional Banks Slump on Worries About Bad Loans; Data Storage Stocks Surge
summary: Regional bank stocks lost ground after a pair of banks disclosed issues with bad and fraudulent loans, while data storage stocks gained in the wake of price-target hikes from analysts.

headline: Western Digital (WDC) Stock Trades Up, Here Is Why
summary: Shares of leading data storage manufacturer Western Digital (NASDAQ: WDC) jumped 6.8% in the afternoon session after an analyst at Wedbush significantly raised the price target for the stock, reflecting a positive outlook on the company's future performance.
